# Vellore Enterprises Agent Notes

Use this file as the first project reference before coding in this repo. Update it whenever architecture, tooling, environment variables, important conventions, routes, or known risks change.

## Project Summary

- Next.js 14 App Router website for Vellore Enterprises, a fire safety business in Vellore, Tamil Nadu.
- Main user flows: premium marketing home page, realtime product catalog, product detail pages, inquiry cart, AMC request form, contact form, WhatsApp fallbacks, and a protected admin product manager at `/velloreadmin`.
- Frontend stack: React 18, Next.js App Router, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, custom global design-system CSS, `react-hot-toast`, `react-intersection-observer`.
- 3D stack was removed from the public experience to reduce client weight and build/runtime cost.
- Backend/services: Firebase Auth and Firestore from browser code; Cloudinary signed upload API route for admin product images.
- Customer support uses `support_chats` for session-based bot conversations and authenticated administrator handoff from the Support Chats admin tab.

## Important Files

- `errors.txt`: chronological development-only error log for Firebase, Firestore, Authentication, Cloudinary, Next.js, React, API routes, build/runtime/lint errors, hydration, deployment, CRUD, realtime updates, admin dashboard, cart, contact form, AMC, image loading, environment variables, and related project issues.
- `firestore.rules`: Firebase security rules; public users can read `products` and `categories`, admins can manage catalog/admin data, and public forms can create inquiry/AMC documents.
- `firebase.json`: Firebase CLI config pointing Firestore rules deploys to `firestore.rules`.
- `app/layout.js`: metadata, structured data, global providers, navbar, footer, WhatsApp floating button, toaster.
- `app/page.js`: redesigned homepage with hero, 3D experience, services, PASS method, industries, timeline, featured products, testimonials, emergency CTA.
- `app/products/page.js`: realtime product catalog, search/filter/sort, quick view, cards, cart and WhatsApp actions.
- `app/products/[slug]/page.js`: product detail page backed by the shared realtime product listener.
- `app/amc/page.js`: AMC booking page and form, writes to Firestore `amc_requests`, falls back to WhatsApp.
- `app/contact/page.js`: contact page, map, FAQ, form, writes to Firestore `contact_enquiries`, falls back to WhatsApp.
- `app/about/page.js`: corporate about page, values, milestones, industries, service coverage.
- `app/velloreadmin/page.js`: protected admin dashboard, Google login, admin whitelist, product CRUD, Cloudinary upload, filters, pagination, bulk delete, delete confirmation.
- `app/api/cloudinary-sign/route.js`: server route that signs Cloudinary uploads with `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET`.
- `app/robots.js`: generated robots policy; admin route is disallowed.
- `app/sitemap.js`: generated sitemap for public routes.
- `app/fire-safety-guide/page.js`: AEO/GEO educational guide with comparison table and direct-answer FAQs.
- `app/locations/vellore/page.js`: local SEO landing page with consistent NAP, service areas, and map.
- `lib/seo.js`, `components/JsonLd.js`: shared metadata and structured-data builders.
- `components/SiteAnalytics.js`: consent-gated GA4, GTM, Clarity, and conversion event preparation.
- `components/PwaRegistration.js`, `public/sw.js`: production service-worker registration and offline shell caching.
- `components/ui.js`: shared Section, Button, MetricCard, SkeletonGrid, and EmptyState primitives.
- `components/Navbar.js`, `components/CartDrawer.js`, `components/Footer.js`, `components/WhatsAppFloat.js`: shared shell and contact surfaces.
- `components/PassMethod.js`: static PASS training section.
- `context/CartContext.js`: session cart state and WhatsApp inquiry message builder.
- `hooks/useFirestoreProducts.js`: shared realtime Firestore product listener with loading/error/offline state.
- `hooks/useReveal.js`: shared intersection reveal hook.
- `lib/constants.js`: company constants, product categories, services, industries, admin emails, WhatsApp URL builder, and slug helper.
- `lib/firebase.js`: Firebase initialization, env-var compatibility, admin email whitelist check.
- `app/globals.css`: enterprise design-system tokens, typography, layout primitives, cards, buttons, forms, skeletons, admin inputs, animations, responsive rules.

## Commands

- Install: `npm install`
- Dev server: `npm run dev`
- Production build: `npm run build`
- Start production build: `npm start`
- Lint script exists as `npm run lint`, but Next 14 may require ESLint setup compatibility checks if it fails.

## Environment And Secrets

- `.env.local` is ignored by git. Do not commit secrets.
- Firebase public config reads these first and falls back to the existing public config for compatibility:
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID`
- Cloudinary signed uploads use:
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_API_KEY`
  - `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET`
- Optional analytics and webmaster verification:
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_BING_SITE_VERIFICATION`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_GTM_ID`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID`
- Admin page falls back to existing public Cloudinary values for compatibility:
  - cloud name: `dkrd0zooe`
  - API key: `332133135685411`

## Data Model

- Firestore collections used by the app:
  - `products`: `name`, `code`, `category`, `description`, `features`, `image`, `slug`, `featured`, `price`, `status`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`.
  - `contact_enquiries`: contact form payload plus `status`, `createdAt`.
  - `amc_requests`: AMC form payload plus `status`, `createdAt`.
  - `support_chats`: random `sessionId`, message array, status, assignment, last message, and timestamps.
- Product categories are centralized in `lib/constants.js`.
- Product `features` is expected to be an array in public product cards; admin form accepts newline text and converts it to an array on save.
- Product links resolve with `productSlug(product)` and route to `/products/[slug]`.

## UI And Design Conventions

- Visual style follows the supplied Vellore Executive system: light blue/pink mesh backgrounds, translucent white glass panels, Vellore red actions, 24px radii, responsive executive layouts, and high-contrast charcoal text.
- Typography:
  - Display: `Outfit` via `next/font`
  - Body: `Inter` via `next/font`
- Common CSS utilities/classes live in `app/globals.css`: `glass-panel`, `card-premium`, `product-card`, `product-media`, `input-premium`, `admin-input`, `text-gold-gradient`, `text-fire-gradient`, `btn`, `whatsapp-float`, `canvas-interactive`, `reveal`, `skeleton-card`.
- Keep layouts responsive with `container-pro`, `container-wide`, `section-shell`, and mobile-first Tailwind classes.
- Public client pages use route-level `layout.js` files for server-rendered metadata; do not move metadata into client page modules.
- Forms use explicit labels, accessible error text, `input-premium`/`admin-input`, toast feedback, Firestore write path, and WhatsApp fallback where applicable.
- Prefer shared primitives from `components/ui.js` before adding new styling patterns.

## Client/Server Rules

- Pages/components using React state, effects, browser APIs, Firebase client SDK, or cart context need `'use client'`.
- App Router metadata exports cannot be used from client components.
- Dynamic imports with `ssr: false` are used for 3D/client-only sections.
- API routes under `app/api` run server-side and can use server secrets.

## 3D Notes

- No 3D runtime assets remain in the public UI.
- Keep the homepage and PASS section CSS-only so the interface stays fast and predictable.

## Fixed Issues

- Admin date displays now use `lib/dateUtils.js` so Firestore Timestamp, string, number, missing, or invalid date fields do not crash date-fns rendering.
- Admin product/settings Cloudinary uploads now use the project Cloudinary env values/fallbacks and no-cache signing requests; product reads normalize common image URL fields into `product.image`.
- `app/sitemap.js` no longer reads Firestore during build; sitemap now returns static public routes to avoid Firebase/grpc build warnings.
- Firestore client hooks now use `getDocs` instead of realtime `onSnapshot` listeners to avoid Firebase 11.10 internal watch-stream assertion crashes in development.
- Products created in `/velloreadmin` now appear on `/products`; the shared listener no longer excludes products missing `createdAt`, and the active admin writer saves slug/status/server timestamps.
- Centralized development error logging now lives in `/errors.txt`; future fixes should update the matching log entry and mark resolved issues as `Fixed`.
- Cart `RESTORE` now restores session cart state.
- Product links now resolve through `/products/[slug]`.
- Firebase config now supports environment variables with compatibility fallbacks.
- Product categories are no longer duplicated across public/admin pages.
- Admin dashboard now uses `next/image`; previous unused import is gone.
- Ineffective AMC `_metadata` was removed.
- Public pages and shared components were rewritten with encoding-safe text. README may still contain mojibake.

## Coding Guidance For Future Agents

- Before edits, run `git status --short` and inspect the files you will touch.
- Use `/errors.txt` as the running development error log. Append new errors in chronological order, never overwrite previous entries, and keep the file UTF-8/plain text.
- Every `/errors.txt` entry must use this structure:

```text
==================================================
Date:
Time:
Page/Component:
File:
Operation:
Error:
Cause:
Resolution:
Status: Pending | Fixed
==================================================
```

- When modifying code to fix an issue, update the matching `/errors.txt` entry with the root cause, files modified, attempted fix or final resolution, and status. Mark unresolved issues as `Pending` and resolved issues as `Fixed`.
- Keep `/errors.txt` for development documentation only. Do not import it, route it, render it, or expose it to users.
- Prefer existing constants, hooks, and UI primitives over introducing duplicated arrays or styling.
- Keep customer contact details consistent:
  - WhatsApp/primary phone: `918072264972` / `+91 80722 64972`
  - Secondary phone: `+91 90874 05584`
  - Email: `velloreenterprises7@gmail.com`
  - Address: `164, Vellore Road, Kangeyanallur, Vellore, Tamil Nadu 632006`
- If adding routes, use App Router conventions under `app/<route>/page.js`.
- If adding shared UI, place it under `components/` and reuse design tokens from `app/globals.css`.
- Keep Firestore writes resilient with WhatsApp fallback for public inquiry forms unless explicitly changing requirements.
- Do not change admin authorization casually; current whitelist is `ADMIN_EMAILS` in `lib/constants.js`.
- Update this `.agents` file whenever you add a new route, collection, env var, command, major dependency, or important known issue.

## Suggested Verification

- For UI/content changes: run `npm run build` at minimum.
- For 3D changes: run the dev server and visually check home page desktop and mobile.
- For Firebase/contact changes: verify both configured Firebase write path and fallback WhatsApp message path where possible.
- For admin changes: verify unauthenticated login screen, authorized admin flow, product add/edit/delete, pagination, bulk delete, and Cloudinary upload signature behavior.
- For cart changes: verify add, quantity update, remove, clear, session persistence, product links, and generated WhatsApp message.
